Make sure you do BUILD rather than deploy first, make sure you’re connected to the Internet when you do so, so you get the libraries you need.

After build succeeds (which would mean you got all of your libraries and dependencies resolved), connect to the robot and deploy.

You only need to do it that way once - until the next library update.

Rather than take screenshots of your code, use Markdown code formatting and paste your code into the forums. You start and end the code block with three back ticks. You can include the programming language after the first three back ticks like so:

```java
var x = "foo";
```

Copy pasted text code is much easier for others to work with than screenshots.
